der expectations at the companys height in  it recorded nearly  billion in revenue dominated the rehabilitation surgery and diagnostic services market and employed more than  people at  facilities in every state of the us along with its facilities in the united kingdom canada australia puerto rico and saudi arabia the company was the largest publicly listed healthcare company in the united states based on the number of locations and the third based on revenuecitation needed by mid to late  healthsouth which never had to file for chapter  bankruptcy protection completed its recovery and relisted its stock on the new york stock exchange under the symbol hls the company currently operates one division inpatient rehabilitation the company formerly operated an outpatient rehabilitation surgery center and diagnostics division the company also previously owned and operated several acute care hospitals that specialized in orthopedics but sold all of those hospitals by  the former outpatient division also operated an occupational medicine division until  when it was sold healthsouth also sold its longterm acute care facilities in may  the longterm hospitals contributed around  million in revenue contents  company beginnings  growth  accounting scandal  recovery and the new healthsouth  affiliated companies  offspring companies  previously affiliated companies  references  external links company beginningsedit healthsouth was incorporated in birmingham alabama as a delaware company on february   as amcare inc by its founder richard m scrushy the company opened its first facility in little rock arkansas and one in birmingham later that year in  the company changed its name to healthsouth rehabilitation corporation in  the company went public with its ipo on the nasdaq stock exchange under the ticker symbol hsrc at the end of the companys last investor roadshow presentation in new york city before its ipo scrushy received a standing ovation from the investment bankers in attendance an extreme rarity in september  the company moved to the new york stock exchange and became listed under the symbol hrc by  the company had expanded to  facilities across the us healthsouth finished out  with  million in annual revenue in  the company made its first large acquisition when it bought  hospitals and  outpatient rehabilitation facilities from national medical enterprise for around  million in cash the acquisition doubled the companys annual revenue to  billion and also made healthsouth the nations largest provider of rehabilitative care in  healthsouth further expanded when it announced it would buy fellow birminghambased relife for  million in stock growthedit an aerial view of healthsouths squarefoot  m headquarters campus located on highway  at one healthsouth parkway taken in march  in birmingham alabama throughout the mids healthsouth expanded rapidly through mergers and acquisitions in  the company changed its name to healthsouth corporation to better reflect its diversified interests in healthcare on august   healthsouth ceo richard scrushy announced that healthsouth was going to build a new headquarters on us highway  in birmingham the new corporate campus was to be built on  acres  m of land that the company had bought from southern company earlier that year the corporate campus plans included a five story headquarters building with a connecting conference center and parking deck healthsouths h logo in black the logo first appeared in  as the recognizable symbol for the company in january  the company entered the surgery center business with its  million acquisition of surgical health corporation one month later the company acquired novacares entire rehabilitational hospital business for  million in cash in  the company expanded into diagnostics with its purchase of health images inc in the beginning of  the company adopted the slogan the healthcare company of the st century less than a year later the company adopted the h logo as its corporate identity healthsouth made its largest acquisition yet when it purchased horizoncms for  billion in  a few months later after the acquisition healthsouth sold the longterm care assets of horizoncms it did not need to integrated health services for  billion in cash healthsouth along with many healthcare publications called this the deal of the century also in february  the company finally moved into its new corporate headquarters the headquarters building itself contained a company store and museum healthsouth continued on its acquisition spree through  by purchasing the majority of columbiahcas surgical division in  the company announced it would along with oracle corporation build the worlds first alldigital hospital on its corporate campus the  story structure was meant as a replacement for its aging healthsouth medical center in downtown birmingham construction began soon after on the new healthsouth medical center accounting scandaledit see also creative accounting the first of healthsouths accounting problems surfaced in late  after ceo richard m scrushy sold  million in stock several days before the company posted a large loss healthsouth was accused by the us securities and exchange commission sec of an accounting scandal where the companys earnings were falsely inflated by  billion in  scrushy allegedly instructed the companys senior officers and accountants to falsify company earnings reports in order to meet investor expectations and control the price of the companys stock the fraud continued for seven years in certain fiscal years the companys income was overstated by as much as  the  billion represents more than  of the companys total assets at one point the companys corporate taxes—based on its fraudulent earnings—were higher than its actual earnings in  healthsouth was accused of violation of the securities exchange act by failing to disclose negative trends and misrepresenting companys financial information in march  healthsouths ceo richard m sc